  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-2" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">About the work</h2>
  
  

  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Early market engagement
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Who the specialist will work with
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          The existing team is comprised of contract and Civil Service resources. The specialist will be expected to be embedded into the Digital team as well as working with the other members of the business.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          What the specialist will work on
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          •Implement high-level technical requirements in a reliable, scalable and performant way<br>•provide coaching and mentoring to more junior colleagues<br>•ensure due technical consideration is given to make processes repeatable, scalable and secure<br>•have deep technical knowledge and experience in DevOps environments, providing support to delivery teams and solving complex problems<br>•Attend all associated Agile ceremonies and make use of collaborative tooling (Slack, Confluence, Jira)<br>•Be proactive on identifying improvements.<br>•Be transparent and collaborative when making decisions<br>•Be able to work with clients with low technical expertise<br><br>Some out of hours working may be required during release schedules and hotfixes.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>

